        "guidedSolution": "**Step 1: Identify what we're finding**\nWe need to find the time $t$ when the mass first drops below 5 grams, starting from an initial mass of $P_0 = 100$ grams.\n\n**Step 2: Set up the equation**\nUsing $P = P_0 e^{kt}$ with $P_0 = 100$, $P = 5$, and $k = -6.896 \\times 10^{-3}$ from part (a):\n$$5 = 100 \\cdot e^{-6.896 \\times 10^{-3} \\cdot t}$$\n\n**Step 3: Solve for t using CAS**\n\n**Formula:** $100 \\cdot e^{-6.896 \\times 10^{-3} \\cdot t} = 5$\n\n**Substitution:** solve$(100 \\cdot e^{-6.896\\text{E-}3 \\cdot t} = 5, t)$\n\n**CAS answer:** $t = 434.4159329$ days\n\n**Step 4: Interpret the result**\nSince the question asks when the substance will \"first decay below five grams,\" we round appropriately to get 434 to 435 days.\n\n**Final answer:** 434 to 435 days (or more precisely, 434.42 days)",
