        "guidedSolution": "**Step 1: Determine the cost values (y)**\nBased on the pricing structure:\n- $x \\leq 1$: Cost = \\$5\n- $1 < x \\leq 2$: Cost = \\$5 + \\$1.50 = \\$6.50\n- $2 < x \\leq 3$: Cost = \\$5 + \\$1.50 \\times 2 = \\$8.00\n- $3 < x \\leq 4$: Cost = \\$5 + \\$1.50 \\times 3 = \\$9.50\n- $x > 4$: Cost = \\$12.00\n\n**Step 2: Calculate probabilities using the normal distribution**\nUsing CAS with $X \\sim N(3, 1)$:\n\n- $P(X \\leq 1) = P(X \\leq 1) \\approx 0.02275$\n- $P(1 < X \\leq 2) = P(X \\leq 2) - P(X \\leq 1) \\approx 0.15866 - 0.02275 = 0.13591$\n- $P(2 < X \\leq 3) = P(X \\leq 3) - P(X \\leq 2) \\approx 0.50000 - 0.15866 = 0.34134$\n- $P(3 < X \\leq 4) = P(X \\leq 4) - P(X \\leq 3) \\approx 0.84134 - 0.50000 = 0.34134$\n- $P(X > 4) = 1 - P(X \\leq 4) \\approx 1 - 0.84134 = 0.15866$\n\n**Step 3: Complete the table**\n\n| $x$ | $\\leq 1$ | $1 < x \\leq 2$ | $2 < x \\leq 3$ | $3 < x \\leq 4$ | $x > 4$ |\n|-----|-----------|-----------------|-----------------|-----------------|---------|\n| $y$ | \\$5 | \\$6.50 | \\$8.00 | \\$9.50 | \\$12.00 |\n| $P(Y=y)$ | 0.02275 | 0.13591 | 0.34134 | 0.34134 | 0.15866 |",
